column296: Comments.9

column36: Breast Draining  L side was very swellon all the way to behind the armpit, and R side has a little bit too. She can take Ibuprofen 3 times a day with Tynenol in between every 2 hours. Drained about 220 on L, 95 on R.
column66: Breast Draining  Patient feel swelling and painful after the draining 2 days after. 3 residents came in the drained her both breast. 3 tube for left breast and 2 smaller tube for the right breast. Need use supply to wrap her breast tight to try to avoid the fluid.
column96: Surgery Follow-up  The drain getting less and Dr. said it should be fine to let it absorb by her body because more draining with needles in her breast will increase the risk for infection. Need next follow-up appointment next week, if everything's fine then can reduce the frequency to monitor it. And Yvette will arrange the time for patient for the physical therapy, maybe could get back to work on mid Dec.
column126: Follow-up  Dr. PT and Dr. Lai are happy with the body absorbing back the fluid. She will not need followup anymore until next year. Dr. PT advised her that she will continue to have breast surgeon give her a manual exam every year for the next few years. She needs to continue with exercising her arm, the nerve and the lyumphetic cords are damaged during the surgey. It is common to feel tingling and tightness. It will get better with time and exercise. The doctors suggested her to go back to work in the beginning of Jan, but patient and sister seems hesitant about it."
column156: OT  The occupational therapiest make accessment for the patient. She thought the patient needs to do more excises. She made a schedule for the patient.
column186: Axillary Cording will need OT, best time is on Sat. M-F 4pm and later.  6 months f/u for the next 2 yrs.
column214: Everything looks fine after bilateral mastectomy. She will need the 6-month follow-up until diagnosis has been 2 yrs.
column243: Every thing is fine, gave her new prescription for bra and prosthesis. It has been 2 years since diagnosis, she will only need to come back for CBE annually.
column273: missing referral, rescheduled to 5/19 at 8:30 am.
column296: everything is fine.   6/1/2017 9 am see Perez again.

column36: Radiation Follow-up  This is the follow-up appt after the radiation therapy. Patient is being well after the treatment. Schedule to see Dr. Kanji three months later with is on May 1st.
column66: Help Patient to deal with the medical bills during the time when Medicaid is not effective.
column96: Left DXMM was okay. Will be back in Aug/Sep for both side.
column126: back exercise as Dr. Kanji suggested. Come back in 6 months on 10/22.
column156: survivorship clinic with Dr. Robinson, review everything and she feels more calm and comfortable about her life after cancer. Dr recommended for DEXA scan too.
column186: 6 mo BL DXMM, benign cal and post lumpectomy changes.
column214: 6 mo L DXMM in Feb 2016 and do arm exercise
column243: 6mo BL DXMM is needed
column273: use aquaphor for sensitive nipple, it's normal after XRT. Aug BLMM, after that it will be 2 years mark, so only need MMG annually.
column296: Ivy & Shuping   lab needed today  dexa, bidxmm & f/u w/ dr. wong& dr.perez in 6mth  advise pcp for back pain referral.

column36: schedule housing application and follow-up on financial assistance application.
column66: Doctor changed schedule last minute but did not contact her or reschedule her. So we rescheduled next week for her.
column96: She did not want to take the full chemotherapy. But the doctor told her that it's not proper to do it. The patient needs liver check. Mercy will contact her.
column126: She was feeling very sick after chemo, but her husband was not reachable and did not have a thermometer at home. I talked to Kathy Power, PA and Susan McDunn the medicine oncologist, that she needs to go to ER if she has fever, if not and still very bad next morning she should go back to the clinic. We bought a thermometer to her house and checked that she doesn't have fever. So told her if she is still sick in the morning, she should go sees the doctor.
column156: Tumor is about 3cm much smaller and softer, can't feel anything anymore under the arm.   The 5th chemo will be Taxoere, it will give her less nausea and vomiting but take longer time to drip. She will also require to take Dexamethasone or Decadron the day before, the day of, and the day after chemo - 2 in the morning and 2 at night to prevent swelling.   She will need to watch for numbness and tingling in fingers and toes.
column186: performed EKG - normal, go to ER if having chest pain and shortness of breath.   ordered repeat CAT for suspicious cyst.  Scheduled 6/12 to see surgeon and medicine oncologist.
column214: Scheduled CT appt for her tomorrow right after chemo. She worries that she won't feel well or be late for the appt, so i gave her the radiology dept phone number just in case she needs it to contact them.
column243: New MMG and US is scheduled on 7/1, will see Dr. Monahan afterward to discuss surgical plan. Surgery will be in the last week of July or first week of Aug. There are benign hemagioma and cysts in liver, nodule in adrenal gland. Dr. McDunn recommended use hydrocortisone ointment for her puffy eyelid and tearing eye. She also ordered artificial tears for her eye. See Dr. McDunn again on 7/24 10am to discuss about Tamoxifen.
column273: MMG and U/S showed the tumor size is 2.5cm now and LN look normal. Discussed surgical plan, she decided to have mastectomy. Also found out that reconstruction would be covered if she desires. Will come back for pre-op blood work and obtain surgery time on 7/28.
column296: decided surgical plan: R mastectomy with SNB and possible ALND.   She will have 1 or 2 drain, stay 1 night after surgery, and post-op appt 1 week after.  Discussed clinical trial but declined at last.   Go back on 7/21 for pre-op testing and medical consultant due to high blood sugar.

column36: her PCP Dr. Chauhan says that her blood test result is not urgent to be seen again soon, but need to discuss follow-up testing with her.
column66: I informed her about her kidney condition that she needs to see a PCP, maybe refer to an U/S for her kidney to find out what is causing the function level going down. She is also informed to stop taking her BP med. She said she will ask around to see where can she find a doctor around there because I told her she shouldn't quit her job to come back for appointments.
column96: Bummed up the appt with PCP for her U/S result and HTN med.   Gyn recommended 1 year f/u pap or hysterectomy can be an option
column126: Change Rx from Amlodipine to Lisinopril 10mg. She needs to take BP 2/day at wake up and bed time keep record while in China. Come back to see nephologist Dr. Richard Hong (need to call schedule later) and will come back to see Dr. Chauhan on 3/10 9am.
column156: She is not sure if her Medicaid will end in March, it is still active right now. I will check again in March. Ann will help her re-apply the regular Medicaid when she comes in.
column186: help her read the letter and then explanation to her and help her choose the plan.
column214: Informed pt benign Pap result, but she still need 1 year f/u next year. And reminded her she was due for MMG in May this year.

column36: Scheduled appt with Sub and for DXMM

Pt show up with bloody discharge, found Dr Perez to write an order, then Dr. Serena was able to get her in right away. They were worried there's another papilloma in there. U/S was normal but will see Dr. Perez for f/u.
column66: did not have bloody d/c more than once or keep occurring is okay, just come back in 3mo for OV on 1/27 at 8:30 am.
column96: recommended lotions for nipple itchiness, advised not to squeeze nipple. Come back in 6 mo (Oct 2016) for SCMM and OV. Lily has the order, and appt been scheduled.

column36: F/u with Lumpectomy  All the cancer cells has been removed with clear margin. And the 4 lymph node has been taken are negative. Pt need radiation therapy after seeing Dr. Wong. And will need 1 month follow-up with Dr. Perez which has been scheduled on 12/18/2014
column66: Dr. Wong will send specimen for Oncotype testing, result will be back in 7 to 10 days.  2/3 chance is not strong cancer cell, so only RT and AI, 1/3 chance is strong will need RT, AI, and chemo.
column96: She will need RT and AI, but no chemo. There's 3 in 1 patient will have arthritis symptoms with AI, so she will need to take Vit D and osteoporosis med. She had DEXA scan is 9/2014, so she won't need it again. She will see Dr. Wong again after RT is done. Schedule appt with Dr. Kanji.
column126: 6.5 weeks, 33 treatment. 28 whole breast, and 5 boost. Start on 12/29 at 8:30am, everyday except 1/1.
column156: Nipple inverted but was told because of swelling from surgery and also scar tissue pulling it back.  6 mo f/u in March for right breast, and 1 year for left breast.
column186: Continue to have nipple discharge on the surgical side, discharge started prior to surgery. No fever, warm to touch, or signs of infection. I advised the patient to stop squeezing it, and will ask Dr. Perez if she needs to be seen.
column214: Patient waited outside for over an hour for Mercy's transportation. Mercy said pt was no show. Called transportation to ask them to pick her up agian.
column243: Continued to be late and trouble in picking pt up for RT. Had to called transportation many times to reach someone to go get her again.
column273: Trouble persisted. Called and verified she was on the pick-up schedule with correct address and phone number.
column296: Finally Mercy picked pt up and she was on time for RT. There are still concern on waiting and which number to call her. Verified everything with Transportation again.

column36: Pt complained she's being ignored for a whole night and nobody took care of her even she wet her bed. Dr. Perez went to her room and find out what's going on. Pt Navigator helped to calm her down and help communicate with Pt and Dr.
column66: Pt complained about no fresh air in the room and nobody took good care of her. She wanna go out of the hospital and also refused to have any blood draw because she's so upset of the hospital setting and also the nurses. Finally she's calm down and accept not going out.
column96: Pt was scheduled to see Dr. Perez at 11:45am on Thur, but Pt mentioned that if appt would be earlier then her daughter can give her a ride, so PN helped her to rescheuduled to 8:30am so she could have someone to drop her off and pick her up.
column126: F/u with mastectomy  All the cancer cells has been removed and the five lymph node that has been took out are negative. Pt doesn't need radiation. But Pt went to ER on Monday because she drag her drain off and seems there's still some bruise under her armpit and need to wrap one more week and see Dr. Perez. Pt complained about the dressing is too tight and the texture is not good and Dr. Perez said she can't pick what she want or not. She will need to see medical oncology after seeing Dr. Perez next week.
column156: drains are finally removed, no more bruising and will not need bandages anymore.
column186: Dr. Wong suggested for a infusion port, then chemo for 6 sessions, once every 3 weeks. And another medicine for 1 year. She has serious anemia and need to find out the cause before starting chemo. Dr. Wong wanted to schedule colonoscopy and EGD the following week. But after some wait time to schedule patient suddenly change her mood and attitude, she was very irritated and upset about losing hair for chemo. Even after some explanation of support and help she still refuse for treatment. She said that she is old already, she is fine with dying in her 70s.
column214: Opt out Medicaid HMO plan to traditional Medicaid.
column243: Convinced her to take care of her anemia with Samuel Leung, then see another oncologist for second opinion. Dr. Dominic Ho or Dr. Atassi are the choices.
column273: Had not been able to contact her for awhile, but finally got through today. She said that Dr. Leung retired, so she would like to go see Shirley Wong. And I also consulted her about seeing Dr. Ho as oncologist, and made an appointment with him for her on 2/5 3:30pm.
column296: Tried to remind pt the appt with Dr. Ho, but she decided not to go last minutes because he is a man. She says she will not see a man doctor unless I can find a female doctor. Even if the doctor is far away that's okay. So I emailed Dr. Perez for her referral at Loyola.

column36: blood test for surgery clearance
column66: 1 wk f/u with Dr. Schirele. Removed drain no.1, will remove the no. 2 next week. Surgery can be done in a month or so. She will not need anymore saline injection because skin can be added from the TRAM.
column96: 27/40 sections had DCIS, no invasion, close margin, nodes negative. one month f/u on 5/7 11:30am, and f/u with Dr. Perez every 6 months for the next 2 years.
column126: She was determined to get a surgery date set. She is interested/wondered if she need a compressed sleeves for the long flight. 6 to 8 weeks to recover after TRAM surgery. As soon as 2 weeks can fly after surgery. If something happened delayed surgery, there will not be penalty if flight has to be delayed.   MAY 12 at Prentice!!!  5/4 8:30pm f/u pre-op!
column156: NMH dropped Harmony, can't do surgery there. They only accept Illicare and Atena Better Health. Or do it at UIC. Contact person is Khristine Padiernos 312.672.1307
column186: UIC next surgery date is 6/24, need to see Dr. Marco Ellis prior. Fax medical record to 312.413.0495. Possible appt time is 5/13 or 5/27.
column214: Called Harmony and NSPS, Julie submitted pre-auth request should have response by the end of the day to find out if we can have surgery at NMH or not. It could take up to 14 days for auth though.
column243: Can't change plan at HFS again, called the state to authorize change but they said need to work with Harmony. Called Harmony but could not help unless NMH called Provider Services directly. P: 1.800.608.8158. State says if Harmony unwilling to work with us, we need to know the name and contact for that person.
column273: Harmony authed 1 day stay only, clinical will need to be faxed in after she is admitted.   fax: 877.844.8538  phone: 1.800.608.8158 x4487  attn: Mary Cason
column296: R DXMM and 6 mo f/u in Oct 2015.   Schedule with OT to fit compression sleeve before China trip, sometime in late June.  She asked about HER2 testing, but it's only for invasive cancer.

column36: Called insurance with pt on the phone, after many transfer, we were informed that we can't cancel directly and everything must go through her employer. So I told her to call me if she needs help explaining her situation at work.
column66: Called insurance with her to try to cancel it so we can apply Medicaid for her, but insurance company can't do it. It has to be canceled through her work.
column96: Called her friend to remind her and pressure her to cancel insurance to apply for Medicaid because I haven't been able to reach her through phone.
column126: Pt finally gave me her company's phone number so I could talk to her HR. HR says that they never even talked to the pt before and she can't cancel her insurance after 12/31. So I let pt know that she will have to proceed surgery with her employer's insurance.
column156: Pt, friend, daughter, and mom were all here. She was very nervous as usual. Surgery went very smoothly. She was very awake and well afterward. I have never seen her so happy and smiled like that too. F/u with Dr. Perez on the 1/29.
column186: Tis with clear margin. No further surgery is needed. Refer to Dr. Kanji and Dr. Wong. f/u in 1 month.
column214: See Dr. Kanji for RT, will see Dr. Wong again on 4/1 10 am. Hormone therapy after RT.
